headline: With Warren Buffett Done as CEO, Just 3 Stocks Make Up Almost 50% of Berkshire Hathaway
summary: American Express, Apple, and Bank of America make up almost 50% of Berkshire Hathaway’s total holdings. Will that continue now that Warren Buffett has stepped down?
